50enum class ExprPrecedence : int {
51 /*! \brief Identity(e.g., IntImm, Var) and function call(e.g., floordiv, min) */
52 kIdentity = 0,
53 /*!
54 * \brief Multiplication(*), division(/), and remainder(%)
55 * \note floorDiv, floorMod is marked as kIdentity since they are function calls.
56 */
57 kMultiplicationDivision = 1,
58 /*! \brief Addition(+) and subtraction(-) */
59 kAdditionSubtraction = 2,
60 /*! \brief For relational operators < and <= and > and >= respectively */
61 kRelational = 3,
62 /*! \brief For equality operators = and != respectively */
63 kEquality = 4,
64 /*! \brief And(&&) */
65 kAnd = 5,
66 /*! \brief Or(||) */
67 kOr = 6,
68 /*! \brief Unknown precedence */
69 kUnknown = 7,
70};
71
72/*! \brief Utility used for identifying usage of a buffer_var
73 *
74 * \details Find the Buffer object that corresponds to a variable or
75 * allocation, based on the BufferLoad/BufferStore instances that
76 * occur within the allocation's body.
77 */
78class BufferUsageFinder : public StmtExprVisitor {
79 public:
80 static Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> FindUsage(Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage, Stmt body) {
81 BufferUsageFinder visitor(std::move(usage));
82 visitor.VisitStmt(body);
83 return std::move(visitor.usage_);
84 }
85
86 void VisitExpr_(const VarNode* op) final {
87 Var var = GetRef<Var>(op);
88 if (!usage_.count(var)) {
89 usage_.Set(var, {});
90 }
91 }
92
93 void VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) final {
94 VisitBuffer(op->buffer);
95 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
96 }
97
98 void VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) final {
99 VisitBuffer(op->buffer);
100 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
101 }
102
103 void VisitStmt_(const DeclBufferNode* op) final {
104 buffers_declared_.insert(op->buffer.get());
105 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
106 buffers_declared_.erase(op->buffer.get());
107 }
108
109 private:
110 explicit BufferUsageFinder(Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage) : usage_(usage) {}
111
112 void VisitBuffer(const Buffer& buffer) {
113 if (buffers_visited_.count(buffer.get())) {
114 return;
115 }
116 if (buffers_declared_.count(buffer.get())) {
117 return;
118 }
119 buffers_visited_.insert(buffer.get());
120
121 Array<Buffer> arr = usage_.Get(buffer->data).value_or({});
122 arr.push_back(buffer);
123 usage_.Set(buffer->data, arr);
124 }
125
126 // The search result.
127 Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage_;
128 // The buffers that have been visited so far, to avoid duplicate
129 // entries in the search result.
130 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> buffers_visited_;
131 // The buffers declared via `DeclBuffer`. These buffers are excluded from the result because
132 // T.buffer_decl shouldn't be printed for them.
133 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> buffers_declared_;
134};

136/*!
137 * \brief The printer for TVMScript
138 * \details The printer obtain the precedence of the top-level operation when printing each
139 * subexpression to decide whether or not parentheses is needed.
140 */
141class TVMScriptPrinter : public StmtFunctor<Doc(const Stmt&)>,
142 public ExprFunctor<Doc(const PrimExpr&, ExprPrecedence*)>,
143 public TypeFunctor<Doc(const Type&)> {
144 public:
145 explicit TVMScriptPrinter(const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
146 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate = nullptr)
147 : tir_prefix_(tir_prefix),
148 show_meta_(show_meta),
149 annotate_(std::move(annotate)),
150 meta_collector_(&meta_) {}

159
160 protected:

162 String tir_prefix_;
163 /*! \brief whether show meta data */
164 bool show_meta_;

167 /*! \brief meta data context */

169 /*! \brief meta collector */

171 /*! \brief map from Function to GlobalVar */
172 std::unordered_map<const BaseFuncNode*, GlobalVar> func2var_;
173 /*! \brief var collector (var defined by For/Loop/Block) */
174 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*> var_not_in_headers_;
175 /*!
176 * \brief buffer collector
177 * (buffer defined in BufferMap, BufferAllocation and MatchBufferRegion)
178 */
179 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> buf_not_in_headers_;
180 /*! \brief Map from Var to thread env name */

182 /*! \brief Map from Var to Doc */

184 /*! \brief Map from Buffer to Doc */

186 /*! \brief Map from Buffer to Declaration Doc */
187 std::unordered_map<Buffer, Doc, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> memo_buf_decl_;
188 /*! \brief name allocation map */

194 /*! \brief loop stack without annotations */

200 * simple_remap requires:

202 * 2. value is a single Var, which is a loop_var outside the block
203 * 3. The iter range is equal to loop range

206 /*!
207 * \brief Map from variables to the buffers they are used in.
208 *
209 * Used for identifying buffers that should be declared after the
210 * LetStmt or Allocate that generates their data pointer, rather
211 * than in the header.
212 */
213 Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> buffer_var_usage_;
214 /*! \brief Analyzer to simplify some expressions. */
215 arith::Analyzer ana_;

303 /*!
304 * \brief Check if a buffer declaration satisfies:
305 * 1. has only 'shape' and 'dtype' arguments specified,
306 * 2. the shape and strides are not dynamic.
307 * \param buffer The match buffer to be checked
308 */
309 bool IsSimpleBuffer(const Buffer& buffer);

313 /*! Helper functions for loop printing. */
314 /*!
315 * \brief Print a single for loop
316 * \param loop The for loop to be printed
317 */
318 virtual Doc PrintLoop(const For& loop);
319 /*! \brief Print all simple loops in stack into one line using tir_prefix_.grid(). */
320 Doc PrintLoopStack();
321 /*!
322 * \brief Check whether a loop satisfies:
323 * 1. the loop is serial;
324 * 2. the loop has no annotation;
325 * 3. the loop starts from 0;
326 * 4. there is no optional information.
327 * \param for_op the for node to be checked
328 * \return A boolean indicating whether the input loop satisfies the above conditions
329 */
330 bool IsSimpleLoop(const ForNode* for_op) {
331 return for_op->kind == ForKind::kSerial && for_op->annotations.empty() &&
332 is_zero(for_op->min) && !ContainsOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(for_op));
333 }
334 /*!
335 * \brief Check whether the `min` or `extent` of a loop depends on previous loops
336 * \param for_op The loop to be checked
337 * \return A boolean indicating whether the input loop depends on previous loops
338 */
339 bool DependOnPrevLoops(const ForNode* for_op) {
340 auto f_check = [&var_map = this->loop_var_map_](const VarNode* v) { return var_map.count(v); };
341 return UsesVar(for_op->min, f_check) || UsesVar(for_op->extent, f_check);
342 }
343
344 /*!
345 * \brief Print additional info about expr in comment.
346 * \param expr The expression.
347 */
348 Doc PrintOptionalInfo(const Stmt& stmt) {
349 Doc doc;
350 // default annotations
351 if (ContainsOptionalInfo(stmt)) {
352 std::string annotated_stmt = annotate_(stmt);
353 doc << "# " << annotated_stmt << Doc::NewLine();
354 }
355 return doc;
356 }
357
358 /*!
359 * \brief special method to render vectors of docs with a separator
360 * \param vec vector of docs
361 * \param sep separator
362 */
363 static Doc PrintSep(const std::vector<Doc>& vec, const Doc& sep) {
364 Doc seq;
365 if (vec.size() != 0) {
366 seq = vec[0];
367 for (size_t i = 1; i < vec.size(); i++) {
368 seq << sep << vec[i];
369 }
370 }
371 return seq;
372 }
373
374 /*!
375 * \brief dump meta info
376 * \return Doc with meta info
377 */
378 Doc DumpMeta() {
379 if (show_meta_) {
380 return Doc::Text("__tvm_meta__ = ")
381 << (meta_.empty() ? Doc::Text("None") : meta_.GetMetaSection());
382 } else {
383 return Doc::Text("");
384 }
385 }
386
387 /*!
388 * \brief special method to print out data type
389 * \param dtype The data type
390 */
391 static Doc PrintDType(DataType dtype) {
392 return Doc::StrLiteral(runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype));
393 }
394
395 /*!
396 * \brief special method to print out const int64_t scalar
397 * \param dtype The data type
398 * \param data The pointer to hold the data.
399 */
400 Doc PrintConstScalar(DataType dtype, const int64_t* data) const {
401 Doc doc;
402 std::ostringstream os;
403
404 os << data[0];
405
406 if (dtype == DataType::Int(32)) {
407 doc << Doc::Text(os.str());
408 } else if (dtype == DataType::Bool()) {
409 doc << Doc::Text(data[0] ? "True" : "False");
410 } else {
411 doc << tir_prefix_ << "." << runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype) << "(" << Doc::Text(os.str())
412 << ")";
413 }
414 return doc;
415 }
416
417 /*!
418 * \brief special method to print out const double scalar
419 * \param dtype The data type
420 * \param data The pointer to hold the data.
421 * \note this overriden function is created as std::isnan of msvc will complain about int64_t
422 */
423 Doc PrintConstScalar(DataType dtype, const double* data) const {
424 Doc doc;
425 std::ostringstream os;
426
427 os.precision(17);
428 if (std::isinf(data[0]) || std::isnan(data[0])) {
429 os << "\"" << data[0] << "\"";
430 } else {
431 os << data[0];
432 }
433
434 doc << tir_prefix_ << "." << runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype) << "(" << Doc::Text(os.str())
435 << ")";
436
437 return doc;
438 }
439
440 public:
441 static Doc PrintHeader(const std::string& tir_prefix) {
442 Doc header;
443 if (tir_prefix != "tir") {
444 header << "# from tvm.script import tir as " << tir_prefix << Doc::NewLine();
445 } else {
446 header << "# from tvm.script import tir" << Doc::NewLine();
447 }
448 return header;
449 }
450};
451
452/*!
453 * \brief special method to print NDArray in TIR
454 * \param arr the NDArray to be printed
455 * \param os the output stream where the NDArray will be printed to
456 */
457template <typename T>
458void NDArrayToTIR(::tvm::runtime::NDArray arr, std::ostream& os) {
459 int ndim = arr->ndim;
460 int tot_dim = 1;
461 for (int i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
462 tot_dim *= arr->shape[i];
463 }
464 T* data_ptr = reinterpret_cast<T*>(arr->data);
465 constexpr int NUM_PRINT = 20;
466 os << "[";
467 for (int i = 0; i < tot_dim; i++) {
468 os << (i != 0 ? ", " : "") << data_ptr[i];
469 if (i == NUM_PRINT) {
470 os << "...";
471 break;
472 }
473 }
474 os << "]";
475}
476
477Doc TVMScriptPrinter::GetUniqueName(std::string prefix) {
478 std::replace(prefix.begin(), prefix.end(), '.', '_');
479 std::string unique_prefix = prefix;
480 auto it = name_alloc_map_.find(prefix);
481 if (it != name_alloc_map_.end() && it->second >= 0) {
482 while (name_alloc_map_.count(unique_prefix = prefix + "_" + std::to_string(++it->second)) > 0) {
483 }
484 }
485 name_alloc_map_[unique_prefix] = 0;
486 return Doc::Text(unique_prefix);
487}
488
489Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocVar(const Var& var) {
490 const auto& it = memo_var_.find(var);
491 if (it != memo_var_.end()) {
492 return it->second;
493 }
494 std::string name = var->name_hint.operator std::string();
495 if (name.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name[0])) {
496 name = "v" + name;
497 }
498 Doc val = GetUniqueName(name);
499 memo_var_[var] = val;
500 return val;
501}
502
503Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocBufferDeclaration(const Buffer& buf) {
504 Doc doc = Print(buf->shape);
505 bool print_factor_explicitly = false;
506 doc << ", dtype=" << PrintDType(buf->dtype);
507 if (memo_var_.find(buf->data) != memo_var_.end()) {
508 doc << ", data=" << Print(buf->data);
509 } else {
510 // implicitly define data
511 memo_var_[buf->data] = Doc::Text(memo_buf_[buf].str() + ".data");
512 var_not_in_headers_.insert(buf->data.get());
513 }
514 if (!buf->strides.empty()) {
515 doc << ", strides=" << Print(buf->strides);
516 }
517 if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<VarNode>()) {
518 Var elem_offset = Downcast<Var>(buf->elem_offset);
519 if (memo_var_.find(elem_offset) != memo_var_.end()) {
520 doc << ", elem_offset=" << Print(buf->elem_offset);
521 } else {
522 // implicitly define elem_offset
523 memo_var_[elem_offset] = Doc::Text(memo_buf_[buf].str() + ".elem_offset");
524 var_not_in_headers_.insert(elem_offset.get());
525 print_factor_explicitly = true;
526 }
527 } else if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
528 IntImm elem_offset = Downcast<IntImm>(buf->elem_offset);
529 if (elem_offset->value != 0) {
530 doc << ", elem_offset=" << Print(buf->elem_offset);
531 }
532 }
533 if (buf.scope() != "global") {
534 doc << ", scope=" << Doc::StrLiteral(buf.scope());
535 }
536 if (buf->data_alignment != runtime::kAllocAlignment) {
537 doc << ", align=" << buf->data_alignment;
538 }
539 if (buf->offset_factor != 1 || print_factor_explicitly) {
540 doc << ", offset_factor=" << buf->offset_factor;
541 }
542 if (buf->buffer_type != BufferType::kDefault) {
543 doc << ", type=" << Doc::StrLiteral("auto");
544 }
545 if (buf->axis_separators.size()) {
546 doc << ", axis_separators=" << Print(buf->axis_separators);
547 }
548 return doc;
549}
550
551Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocBuf(const Buffer& buffer) {
552 const auto& it = memo_buf_.find(buffer);
553 if (it != memo_buf_.end()) {
554 return it->second;
555 }
556 std::string name = buffer->name;
557 if (name.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name[0])) {
558 name = "buf_" + name;
559 }
560 Doc val = GetUniqueName(name);
561 memo_buf_[buffer] = val;
562 memo_buf_decl_[buffer] = AllocBufferDeclaration(buffer);
563 return val;
564}
565
566/*!
567 * \brief Check if any optional information exists in annotate_ for
568 * a given Stmt.
569 * \param stmt The statement.
570 */
571bool TVMScriptPrinter::ContainsOptionalInfo(const Stmt& stmt) {
572 if (annotate_ == nullptr) return false;
573 return !annotate_(stmt).empty();
574}
575
576/*!
577 * \brief Try to dealloc vars out of space and leave the index to coming vars.
578 * \note It is not a necessary step.
579 */
580void TVMScriptPrinter::TryDeallocVar(const Var& var) {
581 auto it = memo_var_.find(var);
582 ICHECK(it != memo_var_.end());
583 std::string print_name = it->second.str();
584
585 std::string name_hint = var->name_hint.operator std::string();
586 if (name_hint.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name_hint[0])) {
587 name_hint = "v" + name_hint;
588 }
589 std::replace(name_hint.begin(), name_hint.end(), '.', '_');
590
591 auto it2 = name_alloc_map_.find(name_hint);
592 // Skip it if we can not find the name_hint in name_alloc_map_.
593 if (it2 == name_alloc_map_.end()) return;
594 if (it2->second > 0) {
595 name_hint = name_hint + '_' + std::to_string(it2->second);
596 }
597 // Skip it if the name_hint is not equal to how it should be printed.
598 if (name_hint != print_name) return;
599 // Free the conresponding name_alloc_map_ index
600 --it2->second;
601}
602
603Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintMatchBufferRegion(const MatchBufferRegionNode* op) {
604 const Buffer& buf = op->buffer;
605 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
606
607 Doc doc = Print(op->buffer) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".match_buffer(" << Print(op->source)
608 << ", " << memo_buf_decl_[op->buffer] << ")";
609 return doc;
610}
611
612// check if all arguments, except the first two, are specified for T.match_buffer
613// if not, then this match buffer is printed out as T.buffer in prim_func arguments
614// and check whether there are undefined variables in the shape/strides.
615bool TVMScriptPrinter::IsSimpleBuffer(const Buffer& buf) {
616 if (memo_var_.find(buf->data) != memo_var_.end()) {
617 return false;
618 }
619 if (!buf->strides.empty()) {
620 return false;
621 }
622 for (const PrimExpr& shp_i : buf->shape) {
623 if (!UndefinedVars(shp_i).empty()) {
624 return false;
625 }
626 }
627 for (const PrimExpr& stride_i : buf->strides) {
628 if (!UndefinedVars(stride_i).empty()) {
629 return false;
630 }
631 }
632 if (!UndefinedVars(buf->elem_offset).empty()) {
633 return false;
634 } else if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
635 IntImm elem_offset = Downcast<IntImm>(buf->elem_offset);
636 if (elem_offset->value != 0) {
637 return false;
638 }
639 }
640 if (buf.scope() != "global") {
641 return false;
642 }
643 if (buf->data_alignment != runtime::kAllocAlignment) {
644 return false;
645 }
646 if (buf->offset_factor != 1) {
647 return false;
648 }
649 if (buf->buffer_type != BufferType::kDefault) {
650 return false;
651 }
652 if (buf->axis_separators.size()) {
653 return false;
654 }
655 return true;
656}
657
658Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintInlineBufferBind(const Buffer& buffer) {
659 Doc doc;
660 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".Buffer[";
661 if (buffer->shape.size() == 1) {
662 doc << Print(buffer->shape[0]);
663 } else {
664 doc << PrintTuple(buffer->shape.as<ArrayNode>());
665 }
666 doc << ", " << PrintDType(buffer->dtype) << "]";
667 return doc;
668}
669
670// print array out as tuple with parentheses
671Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintTuple(const ArrayNode* op) {
672 Doc doc;
673 doc << '(';
674 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
675 if (i != 0) {
676 doc << ", ";
677 }
678 doc << Print(op->at(i));
679 }
680 if (op->size() == 1) doc << ",";
681 doc << ')';
682 return doc;
683}
684
685Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintCommReducer(const CommReducerNode* op) {
686 Doc doc;
687 int n_var = static_cast<int>(op->rhs.size());
688
689 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".comm_reducer(lambda ";
690 for (const Var& v_lhs : op->lhs) {
691 doc << Print(v_lhs) << ", ";
692 }
693 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
694 doc << Print(op->rhs[i]) << (i == n_var - 1 ? ": " : ", ");
695 }
696 if (n_var == 1) {
697 doc << Print(op->result[0]) << ", ";
698 } else {
699 doc << "(";
700 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
701 doc << Print(op->result[i]);
702 if (i != n_var - 1) {
703 doc << ", ";
704 }
705 }
706 doc << "), ";
707 }
708 doc << Print(op->identity_element) << ")";
709
710 // Remove the vars in `lhs` and `rhs`, because they are the parameters of the printed lambda.
711 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
712 memo_var_.erase(op->lhs[i]);
713 memo_var_.erase(op->rhs[i]);
714 }
715 return doc;
716}
717
718Doc TVMScriptPrinter::Print(const ObjectRef& node) {
719 if (!node.defined()) return Doc::Text("None");
720 if (node->IsInstance<StmtNode>()) {
721 return PrintOptionalInfo(Downcast<Stmt>(node)) << VisitStmt(Downcast<Stmt>(node));
722 } else if (node->IsInstance<PrimExprNode>()) {
723 ExprPrecedence t = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown;
724 return VisitExpr(Downcast<PrimExpr>(node), &t);
725 } else if (node->IsInstance<TypeNode>()) {
726 return VisitType(Downcast<Type>(node));
727 } else if (node->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>()) {
728 return PrintPrimFunc(Downcast<PrimFunc>(node));
729 } else if (node->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>()) {
730 return PrintIRModule(Downcast<IRModule>(node));
731 } else if (node->IsInstance<ArrayNode>()) {
732 return PrintArray(node.as<ArrayNode>());
733 } else if (node->IsInstance<BufferNode>()) {
734 return PrintBuffer(node.as<BufferNode>());
735 } else if (node->IsInstance<StringObj>()) {
736 return PrintString(node.as<StringObj>());
737 } else if (node->IsInstance<IterVarNode>()) {
738 return PrintIterVar(node.as<IterVarNode>());
739 } else if (node->IsInstance<RangeNode>()) {
740 return PrintRange(node.as<RangeNode>());
741 } else if (node->IsInstance<BufferRegionNode>()) {
742 return PrintBufferRegion(node.as<BufferRegionNode>());
743 } else if (node->IsInstance<MatchBufferRegionNode>()) {
744 return PrintMatchBufferRegion(node.as<MatchBufferRegionNode>());
745 } else if (node->IsInstance<CommReducerNode>()) {
746 return PrintCommReducer(node.as<CommReducerNode>());
747 } else if (node->IsInstance<TargetNode>()) {
748 return PrintTarget(node.as<TargetNode>());
749 } else {
750 LOG(FATAL) << "Do not know how to print " << node->GetTypeKey();
751 return Doc();
752 }
753}

793#define TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(OpName, OpString, OpPrecedence) \
794 Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitExpr_(const OpName* op, ExprPrecedence* out_precedence) { \
795 Doc doc; \
796 ExprPrecedence lhs_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown; \
797 ExprPrecedence rhs_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown; \
798 /* Get children expr out_precedence */ \
799 Doc lhs_doc = VisitExpr(op->a, &lhs_precedence); \
800 Doc rhs_doc = VisitExpr(op->b, &rhs_precedence); \
801 ICHECK(lhs_precedence != ExprPrecedence::kUnknown); \
802 ICHECK(rhs_precedence != ExprPrecedence::kUnknown); \
803 /* Update out_precedence of current node. */ \
804 *out_precedence = OpPrecedence; \
805 if (lhs_precedence > OpPrecedence) { \
806 doc << "(" << lhs_doc << ")"; \
807 } else { \
808 doc << lhs_doc; \
809 } \
810 doc << OpString; \
811 if (rhs_precedence >= OpPrecedence) { \
812 doc << "(" << rhs_doc << ")"; \
813 } else { \
814 doc << rhs_doc; \
815 } \
816 return doc; \
817 }
818
819TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(MulNode, " * ", ExprPrecedence::kMultiplicationDivision)
820TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(DivNode, " / ", ExprPrecedence::kMultiplicationDivision)
821TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(FloorDivNode, " // ", ExprPrecedence::kMultiplicationDivision)
822TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(FloorModNode, " % ", ExprPrecedence::kMultiplicationDivision)
823TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(AddNode, " + ", ExprPrecedence::kAdditionSubtraction)
824TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(SubNode, " - ", ExprPrecedence::kAdditionSubtraction)
825TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(LTNode, " < ", ExprPrecedence::kRelational)
826TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(LENode, " <= ", ExprPrecedence::kRelational)
827TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(GTNode, " > ", ExprPrecedence::kRelational)
828TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(GENode, " >= ", ExprPrecedence::kRelational)
829TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(EQNode, " == ", ExprPrecedence::kEquality)
830TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(NENode, " != ", ExprPrecedence::kEquality)
831TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(AndNode, " and ", ExprPrecedence::kAnd)
832TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(OrNode, " or ", ExprPrecedence::kOr)

927Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitExpr_(const CallNode* op, ExprPrecedence* out_precedence) {
928 *out_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kIdentity;
929 Doc doc;
930 if (auto* ptr_op = op->op.as<OpNode>()) {
931 std::string name = ptr_op->name;
932 if (name.find("tir.") == 0) {
933 name = tir_prefix_ + "." + name.substr(4);
934 }
935 doc << name << "(";
936 } else {
937 auto* op_gvar = op->op.as<GlobalVarNode>();
938 ICHECK(op_gvar != nullptr);
939 doc << Doc::Text(op_gvar->name_hint) << "(";
940 }
941 std::vector<Doc> args;
942 for (const auto& arg : op->args) {
943 args.push_back(Print(arg));
944 }
945 args.push_back(Doc::Text("dtype=") << PrintDType(op->dtype));
946 doc << PrintSep(args, Doc::Text(", ")) << ")";
947 return doc;
948}

965Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const LetStmtNode* op) {
966 if (!buffer_var_usage_.count(op->var)) {
967 buffer_var_usage_ = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(buffer_var_usage_), op->body);
968 }
969 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = buffer_var_usage_.Get(op->var).value_or({});
970
971 Doc doc;
972 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
973 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".let(" << Print(op->var) << ", " << Print(op->value) << "):";
974 doc << Doc::Indent(
975 4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body));
976 } else {
977 if (memo_var_.find(op->var) == memo_var_.end()) var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->var.get());
978 doc << Print(op->var) << ": " << Print(GetType(op->var)) << " = " << Print(op->value)
979 << Doc::NewLine();
980 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body);
981 }
982 return doc;
983}
984
985Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AttrStmtNode* op) {
986 Doc doc;
987 if (op->node.defined()) {
988 // merge attr with realize when possible
989 if (op->node->IsInstance<BufferNode>() && op->attr_key == "realize_scope" &&
990 op->body->IsInstance<BufferRealizeNode>()) {
991 const auto* realize = Downcast<BufferRealize>(op->body).get();
992 if (realize->buffer.same_as(op->node)) {
993 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
994 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".realize(" << Print(realize->buffer)
995 << Print(realize->bounds) << ", " << Print(op->value);
996 if (!is_one(realize->condition)) {
997 doc << ", " << Print(realize->condition);
998 }
999 doc << "):" << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(realize->body));
1000 } else {
1001 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".realize(" << Print(realize->buffer) << Print(realize->bounds)
1002 << ", " << Print(op->value);
1003 if (!is_one(realize->condition)) {
1004 doc << ", " << Print(realize->condition);
1005 }
1006 doc << ")" << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(realize->body);
1007 }
1008 return doc;
1009 }
1010 }
1011 // concise thread env
1012 if (op->node->IsInstance<IterVarNode>() &&
1013 (op->attr_key == "thread_extent" || op->attr_key == "virtual_thread")) {
1014 const auto* iter_var = Downcast<IterVar>(op->node).get();
1015 var_not_in_headers_.insert(iter_var->var.get());
1016 var_env_map_[iter_var->var] = iter_var->thread_tag;
1017 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1018 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".launch_thread(" << Print(iter_var->var) << ", "
1019 << Print(op->value) << "):";
1020 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1021 } else {
1022 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".launch_thread(" << Print(iter_var->var) << ", " << Print(op->value)
1023 << ")";
1024 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
1025 }
1026 TryDeallocVar(iter_var->var);
1027 return doc;
1028 }
1029 }
1030 // default
1031 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1032 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".attr(" << Print(op->node) << ", "
1033 << Doc::StrLiteral(op->attr_key) << ", " << Print(op->value) << "):";
1034 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1035 } else {
1036 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".attr(" << Print(op->node) << ", " << Doc::StrLiteral(op->attr_key)
1037 << ", " << Print(op->value) << ")";
1038 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
1039 }
1040 return doc;
1041}
1042
1043Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AssertStmtNode* op) {
1044 Doc doc;
1045 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1046 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".Assert(" << Print(op->condition) << ", "
1047 << Print(op->message) << "):";
1048 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1049 } else {
1050 doc << "assert " << Print(op->condition) << ", " << Print(op->message);
1051 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
1052 }
1053 return doc;
1054}

1069namespace {
1070
1071bool IsAllocateDeclBufferPattern(const AllocateNode* allocate) {
1072 const Var& buffer_var = allocate->buffer_var;
1073 const DeclBufferNode* decl_buffer = allocate->body.as<DeclBufferNode>();
1074 if (!decl_buffer) {
1075 return false;
1076 }
1077 const Buffer& buffer = decl_buffer->buffer;
1078 if (!buffer_var.same_as(buffer->data)) {
1079 return false;
1080 }
1081 if (allocate->dtype != buffer->dtype) {
1082 return false;
1083 }
1084 if (!is_one(allocate->condition)) {
1085 return false;
1086 }
1087 if (allocate->annotations.size()) {
1088 return false;
1089 }
1090 if (allocate->extents.size() != buffer->shape.size()) {
1091 return false;
1092 }
1093 tir::ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
1094 for (size_t i = 0, n = allocate->extents.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1095 if (!expr_equal(allocate->extents[i], buffer->shape[i])) {
1096 return false;
1097 }
1098 }
1099 return true;
1100}
1101
1102} // namespace
1103
1104Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AllocateNode* op) {
1105 var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->buffer_var.get());
1106
1107 if (!buffer_var_usage_.count(op->buffer_var)) {
1108 buffer_var_usage_ = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(buffer_var_usage_), op->body);
1109 }
1110 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = buffer_var_usage_.Get(op->buffer_var).value_or({});
1111
1112 if (buffer_usage.empty()) {
1113 if (IsAllocateDeclBufferPattern(op)) {
1114 // As a syntax sugar, we identify the pattern of Allocate and DeclBuffer and print a single
1115 // DeclBuffer statement. It is intentionally to call `Print` instead of `PrintBody` here to
1116 // delegate the printing of the current node to `DeclBufferNode` while maintaining the
1117 // same value of `current_num_` and `num_child_`.
1118 return Print(op->body);
1119 }
1120 }
1121
1122 auto storage_scope = GetPtrStorageScope(op->buffer_var);
1123 Doc func_call;
1124 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".allocate(" << Print(op->extents) << ", " << PrintDType(op->dtype)
1125 << ", " << Print(storage_scope);
1126 if (!is_one(op->condition)) {
1127 func_call << ", " << Print(op->condition);
1128 }
1129 if (!op->annotations.empty()) {
1130 func_call << ", annotations={";
1131 func_call << PrintAnnotations(op->annotations);
1132 func_call << "}";
1133 }
1134 func_call << ")";
1135
1136 Doc doc;
1137 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1138 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << Print(op->buffer_var) << ":";
1139 doc << Doc::Indent(
1140 4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body));
1141 } else {
1142 doc << Print(op->buffer_var) << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1143 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body);
1144 }
1145 TryDeallocVar(op->buffer_var);
1146 return doc;
1147}
1148
1149Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AllocateConstNode* alloc) {
1150 std::stringstream ss;
1151 ICHECK(alloc->data) << "Should be presented";
1152 const auto& data = alloc->data.value();
1153
1154 if (alloc->dtype.is_int()) {
1155 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 8) {
1156 NDArrayToTIR<int8_t>(data, ss);
1157 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1158 NDArrayToTIR<int16_t>(data, ss);
1159 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1160 NDArrayToTIR<int32_t>(data, ss);
1161 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1162 NDArrayToTIR<int64_t>(data, ss);
1163 } else {
1164 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1165 }
1166 } else if (alloc->dtype.is_uint()) {
1167 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 8) {
1168 // NDArrayToTIR<uint8_t>(data, ss);
1169 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1170 NDArrayToTIR<uint16_t>(data, ss);
1171 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1172 NDArrayToTIR<uint32_t>(data, ss);
1173 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1174 NDArrayToTIR<int64_t>(data, ss);
1175 } else {
1176 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1177 }
1178 } else if (alloc->dtype.is_float()) {
1179 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1180 NDArrayToTIR<int16_t>(data, ss);
1181 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1182 NDArrayToTIR<float>(data, ss);
1183 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1184 NDArrayToTIR<double>(data, ss);
1185 } else {
1186 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1187 }
1188 } else {
1189 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1190 }
1191 auto ndarray_str = ss.str();
1192
1193 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc->buffer_var.get());
1194
1195 if (!buffer_var_usage_.count(alloc->buffer_var)) {
1196 buffer_var_usage_ = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(buffer_var_usage_), alloc->body);
1197 }
1198 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = buffer_var_usage_.Get(alloc->buffer_var).value_or({});
1199
1200 Doc func_call;
1201 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".allocate_const(" << ndarray_str << ", " << PrintDType(alloc->dtype)
1202 << ", " << Print(alloc->extents) << ")";
1203
1204 Doc doc;
1205 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc->buffer_var.get());
1206 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1207 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << Print(alloc->buffer_var) << ":";
1208 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage)
1209 << PrintBody(alloc->body));
1210 } else {
1211 doc << Print(alloc->buffer_var) << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1212 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(alloc->body);
1213 }
1214 return doc;
1215}
1216
1217Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const DeclBufferNode* op) {
1218 const Buffer& buffer = op->buffer;
1219 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buffer.get());
1220 Doc buffer_name = Print(op->buffer);
1221 Doc func_call;
1222 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".decl_buffer(" << memo_buf_decl_.at(buffer) << ")";
1223
1224 Doc doc;
1225 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1226 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << buffer_name << ":";
1227 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1228 } else {
1229 doc << buffer_name << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1230 doc << PrintBody(op->body);
1231 }
1232 return doc;
1233}

1235Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const IfThenElseNode* op) {
1236 Doc doc;
1237 doc << "if " << Print(op->condition) << ":";
1238 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->then_case));
1239 if (!is_one(op->condition) && op->else_case.defined()) {
1240 doc << Doc::NewLine();
1241 doc << "else:" << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->else_case));
1242 }
1243 return doc;
1244}

1249 stmts.push_back(Print(stmt));
1250 }
1251 return PrintSep(stmts, Doc::NewLine());
1252}

1254Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const EvaluateNode* op) {
1255 if (auto* call = op->value.as<CallNode>()) {
1256 if (call->op.same_as(builtin::assume())) {
1257 Doc doc;
1258 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".assume(" << Print(call->args[0]) << ")";
1259 return doc;
1260 }
1261 }
1262
1263 Doc doc;
1264 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".evaluate(" << Print(op->value) << ")";
1265 return doc;
1266}
1267
1268Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) {
1269 Doc doc;
1270 var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->loop_var.get());
1271 loop_var_map_[op->loop_var.get()] = GetRef<For>(op);
1272 const auto* body = op->body.as<ForNode>();
1273 bool simple_loop = IsSimpleLoop(op);
1274 if (simple_loop) simple_loop_stack_.push_back(GetRef<For>(op));
1275 // It is a loop that can be compressed, let the loops below print it out
1276 if (simple_loop && body != nullptr && IsSimpleLoop(body) && !DependOnPrevLoops(body)) {
1277 doc << Print(GetRef<For>(body));
1278 TryDeallocVar(op->loop_var);
1279 loop_var_map_.erase(op->loop_var.get());
1280 return doc;
1281 }
1282 // It is a loop that can not be compressed
1283 bool print_above = !simple_loop_stack_.empty();
1284 // print loops above if needed
1285 if (print_above) {
1286 doc << PrintLoopStack();
1287 simple_loop_stack_.clear();
1288 }
1289 if (!simple_loop) {
1290 // print current loop if needed
1291 Doc current_loop;
1292 current_loop << PrintLoop(GetRef<For>(op));
1293 current_loop << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1294 doc << (print_above ? Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << current_loop) : current_loop);
1295 } else {
1296 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1297 }
1298 TryDeallocVar(op->loop_var);
1299 loop_var_map_.erase(op->loop_var.get());
1300 return doc;
1301}
1302
1303Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const PrefetchNode* op) {
1304 Doc doc;
1305 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".prefetch(" << Print(op->buffer) << ", " << Print(op->bounds) << ")";
1306 return doc;
1307}

1309Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const WhileNode* op) {
1310 Doc doc;
1311 doc << "while " << Print(op->condition) << ":";
1312 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1313 return doc;
1314}

1359
1360/*! Helper functions for block printing. */
1361Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVar(const IterVar& iter_var, const PrimExpr& value) {
1362 Doc doc;
1363 doc << Print(iter_var->var) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".axis.";
1364 switch (iter_var->iter_type) {
1365 case kDataPar:
1366 doc << "spatial";
1367 break;
1368 case kCommReduce:
1369 doc << "reduce";
1370 break;
1371 case kOrdered:
1372 doc << "scan";
1373 break;
1374 case kOpaque:
1375 doc << "opaque";
1376 break;
1377 default:
1378 LOG(FATAL) << "Unknown block var iter type: " << iter_var->iter_type;
1379 break;
1380 }
1381 doc << "(";
1382 const Range& dom = iter_var->dom;
1383 if (is_zero(dom->min)) {
1384 doc << Print(dom->extent);
1385 } else {
1386 doc << "(" << Print(dom->min) << ", " << Print(dom->min + dom->extent) << ")";
1387 }
1388 doc << ", " << Print(value) << ")";
1389 return doc;
1390}
1391
1392Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVarRemaps() {
1393 ICHECK(!block_var_remaps_.empty());
1394 if (block_var_remaps_.size() == 1) {
1395 const IterVar& iter_var = block_var_remaps_[0].first;
1396 const PrimExpr& value = block_var_remaps_[0].second;
1397 return PrintBlockVar(iter_var, value);
1398 }
1399 Doc doc;
1400 std::vector<Doc> iter_vars, iter_values;
1401 std::string iter_type;
1402 for (const auto& pair : block_var_remaps_) {
1403 const IterVar& iter_var = pair.first;
1404 const PrimExpr& value = pair.second;
1405 iter_vars.push_back(Print(iter_var->var));
1406 iter_values.push_back(Print(value));
1407 if (iter_var->iter_type == kDataPar) {
1408 iter_type += "S";
1409 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == kCommReduce) {
1410 iter_type += "R";
1411 } else {
1412 ICHECK(false);
1413 }
1414 }
1415 doc << PrintSep(iter_vars, Doc::Text(", ")) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".axis.remap("
1416 << Doc::StrLiteral(iter_type) << ", [" << PrintSep(iter_values, Doc::Text(", ")) << "])";
1417 return doc;
1418}
1419
1420Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVars(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1421 Doc doc;
1422 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1423 ICHECK_EQ(block_op->iter_vars.size(), op->iter_values.size());
1424 tir::ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
1425
1426 auto is_simple_remap = [this, &expr_equal](const IterVar& iter_var,
1427 const PrimExpr& value) -> bool {
1428 if (iter_var->iter_type != kDataPar && iter_var->iter_type != kCommReduce) return false;
1429 if (!value->IsInstance<VarNode>()) return false;
1430 const Var& var = Downcast<Var>(value);
1431 auto it = loop_var_map_.find(var.get());
1432 return it != loop_var_map_.end() && expr_equal(it->second->min, iter_var->dom->min) &&
1433 expr_equal(it->second->extent, iter_var->dom->extent);
1434 };
1435
1436 for (size_t i = 0; i < block_op->iter_vars.size(); ++i) {
1437 const IterVar& iter_var = block_op->iter_vars[i];
1438 const PrimExpr& value = op->iter_values[i];
1439 var_not_in_headers_.insert(iter_var->var.get());
1440 if (is_simple_remap(iter_var, value)) {
1441 block_var_remaps_.push_back(std::make_pair(iter_var, value));
1442 } else {
1443 if (!block_var_remaps_.empty()) {
1444 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVarRemaps();
1445 block_var_remaps_.clear();
1446 }
1447 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVar(iter_var, value);
1448 }
1449 }
1450 if (!block_var_remaps_.empty()) {
1451 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVarRemaps();
1452 block_var_remaps_.clear();
1453 }
1454 return doc;
1455}
1456
1457Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockAttr(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1458 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1459 Doc block_attr_doc;
1460 // print predicate, binding, read/write tensor region, annotations
1461 if (!is_one(op->predicate)) {
1462 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".where(" << Print(op->predicate) << ")";
1463 }
1464 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".reads("
1465 << PrintExpandedArray(block_op->reads.as<ArrayNode>()) << ")";
1466 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".writes("
1467 << PrintExpandedArray(block_op->writes.as<ArrayNode>()) << ")";
1468 if (!block_op->annotations.empty()) {
1469 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".block_attr({";
1470 block_attr_doc << PrintAnnotations(block_op->annotations);
1471 block_attr_doc << "})";
1472 }
1473 return block_attr_doc;
1474}
1475
1476// This function is to make sure arguments of T.reads() and T.writes() is not parsed by printer as a
1477// List. Therefore the brackets are removed before and after printing arguments out
1478Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintExpandedArray(const ArrayNode* op) {
1479 Doc doc;
1480 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
1481 if (i != 0) {
1482 doc << ", ";
1483 }
1484 doc << Print(op->at(i));
1485 }
1486 return doc;
1487}
1488
1489Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockBody(const BlockNode* op) {
1490 Doc body;
1491 for (const auto& alloc_buf : op->alloc_buffers) {
1492 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buf.get());
1493 body << Print(alloc_buf) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".alloc_buffer("
1494 << memo_buf_decl_[alloc_buf] << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1495 }
1496 for (const auto& match_buf : op->match_buffers) {
1497 body << Print(match_buf) << Doc::NewLine();
1498 }
1499 if (op->init.defined()) {
1500 Doc init_block;
1501 init_block << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".init():";
1502 init_block << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->init.value()));
1503 body << init_block << Doc::NewLine();
1504 }
1505 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1506 return body;
1507}
1508
1509/*!
1510 * \brief Print the name of a block
1511 * \param block_op The block node to be printed
1512 */
1513Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) {
1514 Doc doc;
1515 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".block(";
1516 if (!block_op->name_hint.empty()) {
1517 doc << Doc::StrLiteral(block_op->name_hint);
1518 }
1519 doc << "):";
1520 return doc;
1521}
1522
1523Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1524 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1525 Doc doc = PrintOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(block_op));
1526 // print block name and block vars
1527 doc << PrintBlockName(block_op);
1528 Doc block_var = PrintBlockVars(op);
1529 // print predicate, binding, read/write tensor region, annotations
1530 Doc block_attr_doc = PrintBlockAttr(op);
1531 // print body
1532 Doc body = PrintBlockBody(block_op);
1533 doc << Doc::Indent(4, block_var << block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << body);
1534 for (const auto& iter_var : block_op->iter_vars) {
1535 TryDeallocVar(iter_var->var);
1536 }
1537 return doc;
1538}
1539
1540Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBody(const Stmt& body) {
1541 int memo_num_child, memo_current_num;
1542 std::swap(memo_num_child, num_child_);
1543 std::swap(memo_current_num, current_num_);
1544
1545 Doc doc;
1546 if (body->IsInstance<SeqStmtNode>()) {
1547 const auto& op = Downcast<SeqStmt>(body);
1548 num_child_ = op->seq.size();
1549 current_num_ = 0;
1550 std::vector<Doc> stmts;
1551 for (Stmt stmt : op->seq) {
1552 stmts.push_back(Print(stmt));
1553 current_num_++;
1554 }
1555 doc = PrintSep(stmts, Doc::NewLine());
1556 } else {
1557 num_child_ = 1;
1558 current_num_ = 0;
1559 doc = Print(body);
1560 }
1561
1562 std::swap(memo_num_child, num_child_);
1563 std::swap(memo_current_num, current_num_);
1564 return doc;
1565}
1566
1567Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintIRModule(const IRModule& module) {
1568 auto* op = module.operator->();
1569 Doc doc;
1570 doc << "@tvm.script.ir_module" << Doc::NewLine();
1571 doc << "class Module:";
1572 for (const auto& x : op->functions) {
1573 func2var_[x.second.operator->()] = x.first;
1574 }
1575 Doc body = Doc::NewLine();
1576 std::vector<Doc> functions;
1577 for (auto it = op->functions.begin(); it != op->functions.end(); ++it) {
1578 if ((*it).second.as<PrimFuncNode>()) {
1579 functions.push_back(Print((*it).second));
1580 }
1581 }
1582 body << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintSep(functions, Doc::NewLine() << Doc::NewLine());
1583 body << Doc::NewLine() << DumpMeta();
1584 doc << Doc::Indent(4, body);
1585 return doc;
1586}
1587
1588Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintPrimFunc(const PrimFunc& primFunc) {
1589 auto* op = primFunc.operator->();
1590 // clear renaming map
1591 memo_var_.clear();
1592 memo_buf_.clear();
1593 memo_buf_decl_.clear();
1594 var_not_in_headers_.clear();
1595 buf_not_in_headers_.clear();
1596 // print signature
1597 Doc doc;
1598 doc << "@" << tir_prefix_ << ".prim_func" << Doc::NewLine();
1599 doc << "def " << (func2var_.find(op) == func2var_.end() ? "func" : func2var_[op]->name_hint)
1600 << "(";
1601 std::vector<Doc> params;
1602 std::unordered_set<Buffer, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> simple_buf;
1603 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1604 var_not_in_headers_.insert(param.get());
1605 auto it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1606 // check if this param is a T.handle
1607 if (it != op->buffer_map.end()) {
1608 // check if this match_buffer has only the first two arguments specified
1609 // and whether the match_buffer is a dynamic buffer.
1610 const Buffer& buf = (*it).second;
1611 if (IsSimpleBuffer(buf)) {
1612 simple_buf.insert(buf);
1613 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
1614 params.push_back(Print(buf) << ": " << PrintInlineBufferBind(buf));
1615 continue;
1616 }
1617 }
1618 params.push_back(Print(param) << ": " << Print(GetType(param)));
1619 }
1620 doc << PrintSep(params, Doc::Text(", ")) << ") -> " << Print(primFunc->ret_type) << ":";
1621
1622 Doc body = Doc::NewLine();
1623 // print buffer_bind
1624 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1625 auto it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1626 if (it == op->buffer_map.end()) continue;
1627 const Buffer& buf = (*it).second;
1628 if (simple_buf.count(buf)) continue;
1629 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
1630 body << Print(buf) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".match_buffer(";
1631 ICHECK(memo_buf_decl_.count(buf));
1632 body << Print((*it).first) << ", " << memo_buf_decl_[buf];
1633 body << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1634 }
1635 // print preflattened buffer map
1636 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1637 auto pf_buf_it = op->preflattened_buffer_map.find(param);
1638 if (pf_buf_it != op->preflattened_buffer_map.end()) {
1639 const Buffer& preflattened = (*pf_buf_it).second;
1640
1641 auto buf_it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1642 ICHECK(buf_it != op->buffer_map.end()) << "Found pre-flattened buffer " << preflattened->name
1643 << " with no corresponding post-flatten buffer.";
1644 const Buffer& postflattened = (*buf_it).second;
1645
1646 // Call Print() without assigning in order to fill memo_buf_decl_.
1647 Print(preflattened);
1648 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(preflattened.get());
1649 ICHECK(memo_buf_decl_.count(preflattened));
1650
1651 body << tir_prefix_ << ".preflattened_buffer(" << Print(postflattened) << ", "
1652 << memo_buf_decl_.at(preflattened) << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1653 }
1654 }
1655 // print body
1656 body << "# body" << Doc::NewLine();
1657 if (op->body->IsInstance<BlockRealizeNode>() &&
1658 op->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>()->iter_values.empty()) {
1659 const BlockNode* block = op->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>()->block.get();
1660 if (block->annotations.empty() && !ContainsOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(block))) {
1661 // Skip print root block
1662 body << "# with " << tir_prefix_ << ".block(\"root\")" << Doc::NewLine();
1663 body << PrintBlockBody(block);
1664 } else {
1665 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1666 }
1667 } else {
1668 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1669 }
1670 // print func attrs
1671 Doc header_attr;
1672 if (primFunc->attrs.defined()) {
1673 header_attr << Doc::NewLine() << "# function attr dict" << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_
1674 << ".func_attr({";
1675 std::vector<Doc> attrs;
1676 for (const auto& it : op->attrs->dict) {
1677 attrs.push_back(Doc::StrLiteral(it.first) << ": " << Print(it.second));
1678 }
1679 header_attr << PrintSep(attrs, Doc::Text(", ")) << "})";
1680 }
1681 // print buffer declarations(buffers not defined by buffer_bind or buffer_allocate)
1682 Doc header_buf;
1683 std::vector<const BufferNode*> bufs;
1684 for (const auto& it : memo_buf_) {
1685 if (buf_not_in_headers_.find(it.first.get()) == buf_not_in_headers_.end()) {
1686 bufs.push_back(it.first.get());
1687 }
1688 }
1689 if (!bufs.empty()) {
1690 header_buf << Doc::NewLine() << "# buffer definition";
1691 std::sort(bufs.begin(), bufs.end(), [&](const BufferNode* a, const BufferNode* b) {
1692 return memo_buf_[GetRef<Buffer>(a)].str() < memo_buf_[GetRef<Buffer>(b)].str();
1693 });
1694 for (const auto& buf : bufs) {
1695 header_buf << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Buffer>(buf)) << " = " << tir_prefix_
1696 << ".buffer_decl(";
1697 header_buf << memo_buf_decl_[GetRef<Buffer>(buf)] << ")";
1698 }
1699 }
1700 // print var declaration
1701 Doc header_var;
1702 std::vector<const VarNode*> vars;
1703 for (const auto& it : memo_var_) {
1704 if (var_not_in_headers_.find(it.first.get()) == var_not_in_headers_.end()) {
1705 vars.push_back(it.first.get());
1706 }
1707 }
1708 if (!var_env_map_.empty()) {
1709 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << "# var definition";
1710 for (const auto& it : var_env_map_) {
1711 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(it.first) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".env_thread("
1712 << Doc::StrLiteral(it.second) << ")";
1713 }
1714 }
1715 if (!vars.empty()) {
1716 std::sort(vars.begin(), vars.end(), [&](const VarNode* a, const VarNode* b) {
1717 return memo_var_[GetRef<Var>(a)].str() < memo_var_[GetRef<Var>(b)].str();
1718 });
1719 for (const auto& var : vars) {
1720 auto type = GetRef<Var>(var)->type_annotation;
1721 if (auto* ptr_type = type.as<PointerTypeNode>()) {
1722 auto* prim_type = ptr_type->element_type.as<PrimTypeNode>();
1723 ICHECK(prim_type);
1724 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Var>(var)) << " = " << tir_prefix_
1725 << ".buffer_var(";
1726 header_var << PrintDType(prim_type->dtype) << ", "
1727 << Doc::StrLiteral(ptr_type->storage_scope) << ")";
1728 } else {
1729 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Var>(var)) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".var(";
1730 header_var << PrintDType(var->dtype) << ")";
1731 }
1732 }
1733 }
1734 doc << Doc::Indent(4, header_attr << header_var << header_buf << body);
1735 return doc;
1736}
1737
1738Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintArray(const ArrayNode* op) {
1739 Doc doc;
1740 doc << '[';
1741 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
1742 if (i != 0) {
1743 doc << ", ";
1744 }
1745 doc << Print(op->at(i));
1746 }
1747 doc << ']';
1748 return doc;
1749}
1750
1751Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintIterVar(const IterVarNode* op) {
1752 Doc doc;
1753 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".iter_var(" << Print(op->var);
1754 if (op->dom.defined()) {
1755 doc << ", [" << Print(op->dom) << "], ";
1756 } else {
1757 doc << ", None, ";
1758 }
1759 doc << Doc::StrLiteral(IterVarType2String(op->iter_type)) << ", ";
1760 doc << Doc::StrLiteral(op->thread_tag) << ")";
1761 return doc;
1762}
1763
1764Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintRange(const RangeNode* op) {
1765 return Print(op->min) << ":" << Print(op->min + op->extent);
1766}
1767
1768Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBuffer(const BufferNode* op) {
1769 const Buffer& buffer = GetRef<Buffer>(op);
1770 return meta_.InMeta(buffer) ? meta_.GetMetaNode(buffer) : AllocBuf(buffer);
1771}
1772
1773Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBufferIndices(const Array<PrimExpr>& indices) {
1774 Doc doc;
1775 doc << '[';
1776 for (size_t i = 0; i < indices.size(); ++i) {
1777 if (i != 0) {
1778 doc << ", ";
1779 }
1780 PrimExpr index = indices[i];
1781 if (const RampNode* ramp = index.as<RampNode>()) {
1782 // specify ramp printing as python index slice
1783 if (auto* stride_imm = ramp->stride.as<IntImmNode>()) {
1784 doc << Print(ramp->base) << ":" << Print(ramp->base + ramp->lanes * ramp->stride);
1785 if (stride_imm->value != 1) {
1786 doc << ":" << Print(ramp->stride);
1787 }
1788 continue;
1789 }
1790 }
1791 doc << Print(index);
1792 }
1793 doc << ']';
1794 return doc;
1795}
1796
1797Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(const Array<Buffer>& aliasing_buffers) {
1798 Doc decls;
1799 for (const auto& buf_usage : aliasing_buffers) {
1800 decls << Print(buf_usage) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".buffer_decl("
1801 << memo_buf_decl_[buf_usage] << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1802 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf_usage.get());
1803 }
1804 return decls;
1805}
1806
1807Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBufferRegion(const BufferRegionNode* op) {
1808 Doc doc;
1809 if (op->region.size() == 0) {
1810 doc << Print(op->buffer) << "[()]";
1811 } else {
1812 doc << Print(op->buffer) << "[";
1813 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->region.size(); ++i) {
1814 if (i != 0) doc << ", ";
1815 const auto& range = op->region[i];
1816 if (!is_one(range->extent)) {
1817 doc << Print(range->min) << " : " << Print(ana_.Simplify(range->min + range->extent));
1818 } else {
1819 doc << Print(range->min);
1820 }
1821 }
1822 doc << "]";
1823 }
1824 return doc;
1825}
1826
1827Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintAnnotations(const Map<String, ObjectRef>& annotations) {
1828 Doc res;
1829 std::vector<std::pair<String, ObjectRef>> anno_list;
1830 anno_list.reserve(annotations.size());
1831 for (const auto& pair : annotations) {
1832 anno_list.emplace_back(pair);
1833 }
1834 sort(anno_list.begin(), anno_list.end());
1835 for (size_t i = 0; i < anno_list.size(); ++i) {
1836 if (i != 0) {
1837 res << ", ";
1838 }
1839 res << "\"" << anno_list[i].first << "\":" << Print(anno_list[i].second);
1840 }
1841 return res;
1842}
1843
1844Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoop(const For& loop) {
1845 Doc res;
1846 res << "for " << Print(loop->loop_var) << " in " << tir_prefix_
1847 << "." + std::string(ForKind2String(loop->kind)) + "(";
1848 if (is_zero(loop->min)) {
1849 res << Print(loop->extent);
1850 } else {
1851 res << Print(loop->min) << ", " << Print(ana_.Simplify(loop->min + loop->extent));
1852 }
1853 if (loop->thread_binding.defined()) {
1854 res << ", thread=";
1855 res << Print(loop->thread_binding.value()->thread_tag);
1856 }
1857 if (!loop->annotations.empty()) {
1858 res << ", annotations={";
1859 res << PrintAnnotations(loop->annotations);
1860 res << "}";
1861 }
1862 res << "):";
1863 return res;
1864}
1865
1866Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoopStack() {
1867 Doc res;
1868 if (simple_loop_stack_.size() == 1) {
1869 res << PrintLoop(simple_loop_stack_[0]);
1870 } else if (simple_loop_stack_.size() > 1) {
1871 std::vector<Doc> vars, extents;
1872 for (const auto& loop : simple_loop_stack_) {
1873 vars.push_back(Print(loop->loop_var));
1874 extents.push_back(Print(loop->extent));
1875 }
1876 res << "for " << PrintSep(vars, Doc::Text(", ")) << " in " << tir_prefix_ << ".grid("
1877 << PrintSep(extents, Doc::Text(", ")) << "):";
1878 }
1879 return res;
1880}
1881
1882Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintTarget(const TargetNode* target) {
1883 Doc res;
1884 res << tir_prefix_ << ".target({";
1885 Map<String, ObjectRef> config = target->Export();
1886 for (auto it = config.begin(); it != config.end(); ++it) {
1887 if (it != config.begin()) {
1888 res << ", ";
1889 }
1890 res << "\"" << (*it).first << "\":";
1891 if ((*it).first == "host") {
1892 ICHECK(target->host.defined());
1893 res << PrintTarget(target->GetHost().value().get());
1894 } else {
1895 res << Print((*it).second);
1896 }
1897 }
1898 res << "})";
1899 return res;
1900}

1902/*!
1903 * \brief The printer for TVMScript with diagnostic
1904 * \details The printer obtain the precedence of the top-level operation when printing each
1905 * subexpression to decide whether or not parentheses is needed.
1906 */
1907class TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic : public TVMScriptPrinter {
1908 public:
1909 explicit TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic(const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
1910 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate)
1911 : TVMScriptPrinter(tir_prefix, show_meta, annotate) {}
1912
1913 protected:
1914 Doc PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) override;
1915 Doc PrintUnderline(const Stmt& stmt, int length);
1916 Doc PrintLoop(const For& loop) override;
1917};
1918
1919Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) {
1920 Doc doc = TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockName(block_op);
1921 doc << PrintUnderline(GetRef<Stmt>(block_op), doc.str().size());
1922 return doc;
1923}
1924
1925Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintUnderline(const Stmt& stmt, int length) {
1926 Doc doc;
1927 // annotation
1928 if (ContainsOptionalInfo(stmt)) {
1929 String underline = std::string(length, '^');
1930 doc << Doc::NewLine() << underline;
1931 }
1932 return doc;
1933}
1934
1935Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintLoop(const For& loop) {
1936 Doc res = TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoop(loop);
1937 res << PrintUnderline(loop, res.str().size());
1938 return res;
1939}
1940
1941String AsTVMScript(const ObjectRef& mod, const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta) {
1942 ICHECK(mod->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>() || mod->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>());
1943 Doc doc;
1944 doc << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintHeader(tir_prefix)
1945 << TVMScriptPrinter(tir_prefix, show_meta).Print(mod);
1946 return doc.str() + "\n";
1947}
1948
1949TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("script.AsTVMScript").set_body_typed(AsTVMScript);
1950
1951String AsTVMScriptWithDiagnostic(const ObjectRef& mod, const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
1952 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate) {
1953 ICHECK(mod->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>() || mod->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>());
1954 Doc doc;
1955 doc << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintHeader(tir_prefix)
1956 << TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic(tir_prefix, show_meta, annotate).Print(mod);
1957 return doc.str() + "\n";
1958}
1959
1960TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("script.AsTVMScriptWithDiagnostic").set_body_typed(AsTVMScriptWithDiagnostic);
